Author: Tristan J Philippe
Text: So I graduated from a very small high school I think I walked the stage with 7 others at most  and I have a pretty great relationship with the former Pricipal. We actually went on a day trip to the beach with another former student right before the pandemic hit. Anyways her home phone is set up as a private number so if she needs to call a student she can keep her privacy. Obviously we have each others cell but she typically calls from home and is the only private number that ever calls me. Until the faculty of my new university started working from home. Yesterday I answered the phone with a very snarky and sarcastic comment about abandonment only to find out it was the UNIVERSITY that had just accepted me calling. I almost cried. My former principal called immediately after I texted her to laugh at me and help with damage control.

Text: I just realized a 3hrs class was tolerable because of our small moments with friends in between hugging each other before class<comma> laughing because someone is asleep<comma> writing on each others notebooks<comma> whispering stories to each other that we couldnt wait for the end of class to tell<comma> saying sh<comma> sun louu to shift a distracted friends focus back on an important point<comma> short visits to café instead of the bathroom in 5minute breaks and sneaking in snacks. Now with online classes<comma> when were home and could have entire feasts while taking classes or talk in whatsapp chats meanwhile<comma> goofing just isnt the same and the class just isnt the same. It was these physical moments we never valued<comma> that actually helped us survive. I knew friends were the best part of college <comma> I never knew they were everything.
